    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Dealing With D.S.L.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Barbara Michalak letter on May 4 article questions high cost of DSL phone service for Internet use</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I think that the cost of D.S.L. should have been addressed in the article. What is the justification for the extra $50 a month for what is, after installation, essentially a phone company add-on? With our single phone line and two computers and many offers of free installation, I would try the service in a minute if it was even $30 a month, instead of $50.</p>
        <p>BARBARA MICHALAK  New York</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
